Package: radolanr
Type: Package
Title: This package offers functions to read radolan data and to create information of spatial and temporal variability of rain for sites given as points or polygons given as shape files
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Rikard", "Gra√ü", , "rikardg@web.de", role = c("aut","cre"),
           comment = c(""))
  )
Description: This package offers functions to read radolan data and to create information of spatial and temporal variability of rain for sites given as points or polygons given as shape files.
    Find two usecases in the github reposiory
    1) creating timeseries of radolan data and compare it with data measured by weather stations
    2) estimate spatial distribution of rainfall at points of interest given in a polygonlayer
    find more information here: https://github.com/Blizno/radolanr/
